AB  - The prediction of single and multiple Pareto or translated exponential observables is addressed within a Bayesian framework. In particular the probability that a given fraction out of a finite number of potential observables be in a prescribed finite or infinite interval is calculated. This generalizes previous work which we restricted to the one-sided infinite interval case.
